  "text": "where t d denotes the time interval (in seconds) before the first photons arrive on the specific sample location. In the data of Fig. 4 , t d is of the order of 1.5-2 hours for panel [CITATION_1] and of 3-3.5 hours for panel [CITATION_2] . The last modification is related to a saturation coverage of the adsorbed molecules. Equations (15) and (16) describe a molecular coverage and density that increase without a limit. This is physically unreasonable. We will therefore make the assumption that both Θ mol (t) and N mol (t) reach a plateau at Θ mol max and N mol max . These values will be considered as a partially free parameter in our model with a lower limit at 0.022 for Θ mol max and at 1.49 × 10 13 cm -2 for N mol max . Provided that t d is of the order of several minutes or larger (typical for an ARPES experiment), the exact values of the saturation coverage and saturation density modify only slightly the time-dependent quantities expressed by equations (12)- (14).",
